heat/engine/clients/os/octavia.py.message:
Maybe we should do

try:
  from octaviaclient.api.exceptions import OctaviaClientException
except ImportError:
  from octaviaclient.api.v2.octavia import OctaviaClientException

The reason is that things get messy when you import _everything_ that way. It's better to see what module something came from.

If you really want to work around that you could do:

try:
  from octaviaclient.api import exceptions as client_exceptions
except ImportError:
  from octaviaclient.api.v2 import octavia as client_exceptions

